Write a kubernetes controller in golang. Use github.com/tristanscholten/kube-greencosts for the mod. Use OperatorSDK for this. Make the crds with greencosts.hstr.nl domain. Make some CRDs for this: EnergyPriceSource, this should have a spec like
spec:
  provider: customProvider
  biddingZone: NL
  currency: EUR
  refreshSchedule: "30 13 * * *"
  cacheTTL: 38h

And this should scrape custom energyprovider api's. The prices should be reflected in the status field per 30 minutes. Like:

status:
  lastUpdated: "2026-05-15T13:45:00+02:00"
  prices:
    - start: "2026-05-16T00:00:00+02:00"
      end: "2026-05-16T00:30:00+02:00"
      eurPerMWh: 42.10
    - start: "2026-05-16T00:30:00+02:00"
      end: "2026-05-16T01:00:00+02:00"
      eurPerMWh: -6.30

Also make the CRD EnergyAwareCronJob. In the spec, there should be the normal CronJob fields for jobTemplate, which should be imported from the official kubernetes CronJob types. It should look like:

spec:
  energyPriceSource: <energypricesource resource>
  deadline: "07:00"
  earliestStart: "00:00"
  latestStart: "06:00"
  timeZone: "Europe/Amsterdam"

  schedulePolicy:
    priceWeight: 0.7
    avoidPeakHours: true
    preferNegativePrices: true

  fallback:
    runAt: "06:30"
    whenPriceDataMissing: true
  jobTemplate: ....

And one more CRD:
kind: HibernatePolicy
metadata:
  name: dev-tst-acc-hibernation
spec:
  selector:
    namespaceSelector:
      matchExpressions:
        - key: kubernetes.io/environment
          operator: In
          values: ["dev", "tst", "acc"]

  idleDetection:
    noIngressRequestsFor: 30m
    cpuBelow: "50m"
    networkBelow: "1Mi"
    ignoreDuring:
      - weekdays: [Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri]
        from: "09:00"
        until: "18:00"
        timezone: Europe/Amsterdam

  action:
    scaleDeploymentsToZero: true
    snapshotPVCs: false
    wakeOnHttp: true